{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Json Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Json Filter</h1>

<p>Serializes a value to its JSON representation.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ value | json }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "hello" | json }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> "hello"</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ 42 | json }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 42</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ nil | json }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> null</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>The output is marked as a safe string to prevent HTML-escaping of the JSON content (e.g. angle brackets in strings). Strings are output with Go's <code>%q</code> formatting (double-quoted with escape sequences). Boolean values are rendered as <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>.</p>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/raw">raw</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/escape">escape</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
